<style>
  .article_column-quarter {
    width: calc(25% - 37.5px);
  }
  .article_column-quarter .article_column-image {
    height: 260px;
  }
  @media(max-width: 1450px) {
    .article_column-quarter {
      width: calc(25% - 22.5px);
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 1250px) {
    .article_column-quarter {
        width: calc(50% - 15px);
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 750px) {
    .article_column-quarter {
        width: 100%;
        gap: 30px;
    }
  }
</style>
<div class="rebranding_container block-flex-wrap block-gap-50">
  <div class="rebranding-section-title block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center">
    <h2 class="h2-heading-ss w-100">
      Common    
      <span class="h2-heading-pp">
        authentication mistakes
      </span>
    </h2>
    <p class="body-text block-max-width">
      When trying to authenticate a Louis Vuitton bag, overlooking key details can lead to misidentification. Here are some common mistakes to avoid during a Louis Vuitton authenticity check:
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="article_columns-wrapp block-flex-wrap block-gap-50 block-flex-start-center">
    <div class="article_column article_column-quarter block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "lv_common-authentication-mistakes-1.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="To avoid mistakes during Louis Vuitton bag authentication, pay attention to the bag's monogram pattern">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Monogram Confusion</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
         The iconic Louis Vuitton monogram is often imitated. Mistaking it for similar patterns or failing to notice slight inconsistencies is a frequent error. A trained eye or a <strong>Louis Vuitton authentication service</strong> can help identify the differences
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-quarter block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "lv_common-authentication-mistakes-2.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="To avoid mistakes during Louis Vuitton bag authentication, pay attention to the bag's date code">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Date Code Misreading</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Many people misinterpret the date code, assuming it's proof of authenticity. However, fakes often use convincing codes. Always verify the date format using a trusted <strong>Louis Vuitton date code guide</strong> or conduct a <strong>Louis Vuitton serial number check</strong>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-quarter block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "lv_common-authentication-mistakes-3.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="To avoid mistakes during Louis Vuitton bag authentication, pay attention to the signs of wear or damage">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Ignoring Damage or Wear</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Signs of poor construction, peeling leather, or cheap materials can indicate a fake. Don't assume wear means authenticity — <strong>how to spot fake Louis Vuitton</strong> often starts with spotting poor quality, not just age.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-quarter block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image back-image-style" src="{{ "lv_common-authentication-mistakes-4.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="To avoid mistakes during Louis Vuitton bag authentication, pay attention to the bag's hardware and stitching">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Overlooking Hardware & Stitching</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Hardware should be solid, engraved, and aligned. Loose stitching, weak threads, or missing engravings are red flags. A close-up inspection is a crucial part of a thorough <strong>Louis Vuitton verification service</strong>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

